mil-hdbk-61 pack — content licence
===================================

This pack is derived from:
    MIL-HDBK-61B — Department of Defense Handbook: Configuration Management Guidance
    DoD, 61B, 7 April 2020 (cataloged with Change 1, 15 Aug 2025)

Source licence: Public Domain (US Government work); Distribution A  (tier 1 — see ../../docs/SOURCE-VETTING.md)
No source-material download link is published (see ../../docs/LICENSING.md).

This source is a work of the United States Government, prepared by the Department of
Defense, and is therefore NOT subject to copyright protection in the United States
(17 U.S.C. 105). It carries Distribution Statement A (approved for public release;
distribution is unlimited). It is in the public domain: anyone may reproduce,
transform, and redistribute it for any purpose, including commercially, without
permission. Attribution to DoD is provided as a courtesy (see the repository NOTICE),
not as a legal obligation. DoD does not endorse this pack or its authors.

ADVISORY-GUIDANCE STATUS: MIL-HDBK-61B is explicitly a guidance handbook. It cannot be
cited as a contractual requirement; contractual CM obligations come from the tailored
SAE EIA-649-1 requirements and the citing acquisition documents.

THIRD-PARTY MATERIAL CAVEAT: MIL-HDBK-61B adopts, references, and is the DoD
application/tailoring layer over the SAE EIA-649 standard suite — SAE EIA-649
(Configuration Management Standard), SAE EIA-649-1 (Configuration Management
Requirements for Defense Contracts), and GEIA-HB-649 / GEIA-HB-649A (implementation and
tailoring guides) — and refers to ISO 9000, ISO 10007, ISO/IEC/IEEE 12207, and IEEE 828.
Those standards are the copyright of their publishers (SAE / ISO / IEC / IEEE) and are
NOT in the public domain. This pack reproduces none of their requirement clauses, "shall"
statements, or tables. It contains only synthesized, transformed reference notes that
NAME those standards and describe, in original words, how MIL-HDBK-61B applies and tailors
them for DoD CM. (61B itself notes that EIA-649-1 Annex A — the Tailoring Worksheet — is
the one part of the suite usable and quotable directly in contracts; even so, this pack
does not reproduce it.)

NOTE: This file governs the CONTENT of this pack and is independent of the repository's
MIT licence (which covers tooling only — see ../../LICENSE).
